# Decision log maintenance

When you make or implement a **non-obvious implementation decision**, append an entry to `DECISIONS.md` in the **same session**.

## Log when

- Chose between valid approaches (print path, project split, installer tool)
- Rejected an approach after spike or failed attempt
- Resolved ambiguity the Windows PRD did not spell out at code level
- Introduced a pattern others must follow
- Changed a prior approach — mark old entry `superseded`, add new entry

## Do NOT log when

- Trivial renames or formatting
- Decision already in Windows PRD or Tech Stack (link instead)
- Pure product scope change — update PRD, not `DECISIONS.md`
- New library — update Tech Stack Decision Record

## How to write

1. Insert **above** `<!-- Add entries above this line, newest first. -->` in the Log section.
2. Use template from `DECISIONS.md` (5–15 lines).
3. Mention briefly in reply: "Logged decision: …"

Do not ask the user whether to log — just log unless they said not to.
